===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a kneeling person with mouth open for various reasons (e.g., begging 欠, speaking and/or spitting while speaking [[次]], blowing [[吹]], singing [[歌]], desiring [[欲]], being tired [[軟]], vomiting [[歐]]...).

The reversed version of this character is 㒫 > {{zh-l|*旡}} (e.g. 既), which must not be confused with 无.

Similar but unrelated to [[卩]], in which the person kneeling has the mouth shut.

